      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for clarifying. so if the money is sitting with this third party, what happens if something goes wrong right at the end? like if there's a dispute about the condition of the house or a missing document, how does the escrow agent decide who gets the money?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Great question! In the event of a dispute or issue at the end of the house closing process, the escrow agent plays a crucial role in resolving the matter. They act as a neutral third party to ensure that the conditions of the sale are met before releasing the funds.\n\nIf there's a dispute about the condition of the house, the escrow agent will typically refer to the inspection reports and any other relevant documentation to determine if the house meets the agreed-upon standards. If a missing document is the issue, the escrow agent will work with both parties to locate the document or find a suitable resolution.\n\nIn some cases, the escrow agent may involve a mediator or arbitrator to help resolve the dispute. The goal is to reach a fair and mutually agreeable solution that satisfies both parties. If the dispute cannot be resolved, it may need to be taken to court for a final decision.\n\nIt's important to note that the escrow agent's primary responsibility is to ensure that the conditions of the sale are met before releasing the funds. They will not make a final decision on the dispute, but they will facilitate the resolution process and ensure that both parties have an opportunity to present their case.\n\nTo avoid disputes and ensure a smooth house closing process, it's essential to have clear communication,",
